.SS warp
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl warp list|libs|relations|info  |status [\[en]json]\f[R]
SDD-300: Warp management \[en] the warp-solar-system-shaders engine (scenes, libs, and the scene\[->]lib / lib\[->]lib relation graph) read from config/warp-catalog.yaml
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl warp render  [\[en]json]\f[R]
Render a scene (GPU cuda:0 or CPU) \[en] exec-rail-gated; needs a shaders checkout (WARP_SHADERS_ROOT) or prints an honest no-op
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl warp bench  [\[en]json]\f[R]
Benchmark a scene (ms/frame) \[en] exec-rail-gated
.SS chromofold
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl chromofold info [\[en]json]\f[R]
SDD-500: ChromoFold compressed-domain search \[en] print the read-only capability descriptor (ABI version, library, headers, and the per-primitive map incl. the Lane-A fm_count) read from the native packaging/chromofold_capability.json in the resident engine checkout (CHROMOFOLD_ROOT, else WARP_SHADERS_ROOT). Reports the offline state honestly (exit 0) when none is resident.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl chromofold selftest [\[en]json]\f[R]
The no-GPU header-seam self-test: validate the committed reference fixtures\[cq] 4-byte magic + u32-LE version against the engine\[cq]s own capability descriptor (mirroring packaging/seam_check.c). Never touches a GPU or mutates state.
.SS gateway
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl gateway [\[en]addr host:port] [\[en]json]\f[R]
See the handler for behavior and options.
.SS model-serve
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl model-serve start  \[en]model  \[en]vram N [\[en]engine llama-server|vllm] [\[en]port P] [\[en]dialect openai|anthropic] [\[en]device auto|logic|oracle]\f[R]
Launch / stop / list a GPU serve-process model (SDD-902): the ergonomic
front to the jobs-api model-serve job kind.
start places a model on a GPU by free VRAM (the compute plane), launches
llama-server / vLLM, and registers it as a gateway PROXY backend so
/v1/messages + the OpenAI shim reach it; stop cancels (unregister +
release VRAM); background designates the \[lq]background\[rq] alias.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl model-serve stop \f[R]
Additional supported form.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl model-serve list\f[R]
Additional supported form.
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl model-serve background [ | \[en]clear]\f[R]
Additional supported form.
